'''''Mapp and Lucia''''' is a British drama television series that is set to first broadcast on [[BBC One]]. The three-part series, adapted by [[Steve Pemberton]] and directed by [[Diarmuid Lawrence]], is based on [[E. F. Benson]]'s [[Mapp and Lucia|collection of novels of the same name]].<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.theguardian.com/media/2014/feb/28/david-walliams-agatha-christie-drama-bbc | title=David Walliams to star as BBC bags Agatha Christie drama deal | work=The Guardian | date=28 February 2014 | accessdate=4 April 2014 | author=Plunkett, John}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/tv/news/a554561/lenny-henry-steve-pemberton-to-write-new-bbc-one-dramas.html | title=Lenny Henry, Steve Pemberton to write new BBC One dramas | work=Digital Spy | date=28 February 2014 | accessdate=4 April 2014 | author=Jeffery, Morgan}}</ref>

==Cast==
*[[Anna Chancellor]] as Emmeline Lucas
*[[Steve Pemberton]] as Georgie Pillson
*[[Miranda Richardson]] as Elizabeth Mapp

==Production==
''Mapp and Lucia'' was commissioned by [[Charlotte Moore (TV executive)|Charlotte Moore]] and [[Ben Stephenson]] for BBC One.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/mediacentre/latestnews/2014/mapp-and-lucia.html | title=BBC One announces adaptation of EF Benson<U+2019>s Mapp And Lucia | work=BBC | date=28 February 2014 | accessdate=4 April 2014}}</ref> Filming will begin in [[Rye, East Sussex]] in summer 2014.

